Kurdistan was the first Kurdish newspaper. It was first published in April 22, 1898 in Cairo, Egypt by Mikdad Midhad Badirhan, a member of Krdistan Teali Cemiyeti. In 1991 scholar Emin Bozarslan republished and translated in modern Turkish a collection of its issues.[1]
